**Title:** COM - RFID/NFC Community

**Description:** RFID/NFC can be a difficult technology to understand. Come learn how! The community aims to help discover how short-range wireless communication through RFID works and how to utilize or secure it. It also provides insights into various tools and techniques used for reading, storing, replaying, sniffing, scanning, and brute-forcing RFID systems.

**Key Information:**

- **Brought to you by:** Iceman and Gobo42
- **Learning Approach:** 
  - Participants will engage in a Capture The Flag (CTF) challenge designed to cater to all skill levels, from beginners to advanced users.
  - The training will include the use of Long Range HF readers and will involve practical hands-on experience with tools.
  
- **Tools Introduced:**
  - Proxmark3
  - Chameleon Ultra
  - Flipper Zero

- **What to Bring:**
  - A laptop
  - RFID cards for investigation
  - An RFID-capable reading device such as Proxmark3, Chameleon Ultra, or Flipper Zero.
  - Loaner gear will be available on a first-come, first-served basis.

**Hours of Operation:**

- **Monday:** Expo Closed
- **Tuesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Understanding how RFID/NFC technology functions.
- Techniques to read basic NFC tags.
- Using Flipper Zero in RFID/NFC attacks.
- Knowledge of evaluating NFC/RFID systems for vulnerabilities.

**Community Engagement:**
- The community will also feature the availability of a MiniBadge for participants, details of which can be collected at the community booth.

**Desktop Wallpaper:**
- A downloadable desktop wallpaper is available for community supporters.

For further details, participants are encouraged to visit the community booth at the event.